# Intuition
Don't overthink. Free your mind https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5TyHTxANcPw

# Approach
1. Split array by **/**
2. Filter empty elements (empty strings)
3. Then follow 2 simple rules
    **..** - means we go one directory up, in other words we pop element from the **res** array
    **.** - just skip it
Everything else push to the **res** array
And don't forget **/** in the beginning of the response.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(n)$$

# Code
```
const simplifyPath = (path) => {
    const res = [];
    const arr = path.split('/').filter(v => v);
    for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        if (arr[i] === '..') {
            res.pop();
        } else if (arr[i] === '.') {
            continue;
        } else {
            res.push(arr[i])
        }
    }

    return '/' + res.join('/');
};
```

