**71. Simply Path - Solution**

Pseudo Code:
function simplyPath (string path)
1. Input : *path*
2. Declare a stack variable, *s*
3.  Declare string variables, *directory* & *result*
4.  Add '/' to path (why: to mark the end of the last directory if the *path* doesn't end with '/' )
5.  Traverse through *path*
     a. Let current character be *curr*
	 b.if *curr* is not '/' , then concatenate *curr* to *directory* (why: Assuming anything that is not '/' is going to be the directory name, and we handle "." , ".." accordingly)
	 c. else
	     &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - if *directory* is empty or "." , then do nothing
		 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - else if *directory* = ".." , then pop from stack, *s* (why: ".." represent directory up a level. so, the last encountered directory is not required)
		 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - else push *directory* to the stack, *s* (why: anything non-null string other than "." , ".." represent a directory)
		 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - end if
		 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - clear *directory* value (why: to store next directory name)
	  d. end if
6. if stack, *s* is empty return "/"
7. end if
8. while stack, *s* is not empty
     a. Replace *result* with '/' + stack top + *result*
     b. pop from stack, *s*
9. end while
10. return *result*

```
string simplifyPath(string path) {
        stack<string> s; 
        string directory, result;

        path+='/';               

        for(int i=0;i<path.size();i++){
            if(path[i]!='/')
                directory+=path[i];
            else {
                  if(directory.length()==0 || directory==".") {}
                  else if(directory=="..") {
                     if(!s.empty())
                        s.pop();
                  }
                  else               
                     s.push(directory);
                  directory="";
            }            
        }

        if(s.size()==0)
            return "/";

        while(!s.empty()){
            result="/"+s.top()+result;
            s.pop();
        }

        return result;
}
