solutions.content:
- Split ```path``` by the separator ```/```. Note ```path``` is starting with the separator. So first element of the list is empty string.
- Iteratively move fast pointer forward. Slow pointer can be incremented (general case), decremented (```..```) or unchanged (``` ```, ```.```). If it is incremented then copy value from the fast pointer.
- Delete unnecessary tail from the list and join all items of the list into a string. 

```
class Solution:
    def simplifyPath(self, path: str) -> str:
        arr = path.split('/'); j = 1
        for a in arr:
            if a == '..':
                j = max(1, j-1)
            elif a and a != '.':
                arr[j] = a; j += 1
        del arr[j:]

        return '/'.join(arr) or '/'
